    <section id="id12190436">
      <title>ACTIVITY: To be able to describe the functioning of a dynamo as a source of electrical energy [LO 1.3, LO 2.3]</title>
      <list id="id12190643" list-type="bulleted">
        <item>Ask a friend who has a bicycle with a dynamo to bring the bicycle to the class. If this is not possible, you might ask the owner of a bicycle shop to lend you one.</item>
      </list>
      <para id="id15348357">The energy that is generated by a dynamo is, of course, used to light the light bulb.</para>
      <para id="id18457302">A dynamo contains some wires and a magnet. When the bicycle wheel rotates, the magnet generates electrical energy in the wires. The energy flows along the circuit and the light bulb glows.</para>
      <para id="id18140964">Investigate how a dynamo works:</para>
      <figure id="id12181676">
        <media id="id12181676_media" alt="">
          <image mime-type="image/png" src="../../media/graphics1-7baf.png" id="id12181676__onlineimage" height="325" width="214"/>
        </media>
      </figure>
      <para id="id18506508">Use a bicycle with a dynamo:</para>
      <para id="id10221978">1. Pull the dynamo away from the wheel and rotate the wheel.</para>
      <para id="id16405857">2. Bring the dynamo in contact with the wheel and rotate the wheel.</para>
      <para id="id12199353">3. Rotate the wheel slowly.</para>
      <para id="id6433947">4. Rotate the wheel fast.</para>
      <para id="id12181724">5. Keep your eyes on the light bulb continually.</para>
      <para id="id12183164">Formulate the findings that you derive from the practical investigation in well-constructed sentences.</para>
